text: The 1925 San Jose State Spartans football team represented State Teachers College at San JoseSan Jose State University was known as State Teachers College at San Jose from 1921 to 1934. during the 1925 college football season. San Jose State competed in the California Coast Conference (CCC). The team was led by second-year head coach Ernesto R. Knollin, and they played home games at Spartan Field in San Jose, California. The team finished the season with a record of two wins and five losses (2–5, 2–4 CCC).
